channel.title: Consistent players
channel.description:
According to the http://www.google.com/trends/?q=runescape
It shows decay, all directing towards the search term "Runescape" on any google powered search engine.
So as players, do you think the population has been growing or decreasing in the past 6 months? *Not including losing players/bots from the bot nuke.

item.title: Consistent players
item.dc:creator: @the_elve_age the elve age
item.description:
@the_elve_age wrote:

[quote=“m1lkman, post:14, topic:437568”]Times have changed. Players who know what runescape is tell their friends, “runescape.com” not “google runescape”. They download the client and play without opening a browser.[/quote]You would be surprised on how many people still google “Facebook login” just to log onto their Facebook.

And when I tell someone of a website, I usually tell them to google, and first thing to come up click it.

@BloodRayne, thank you.

item.title: Consistent players
item.dc:creator: @bloodrayne bloodrayne
item.description:
@bloodrayne wrote:

[quote=“Miss Silabsoft, post:19, topic:437568”][quote author=m1lkman link=topic=540274.msg3957768#msg3957768 date=1332938260]

[img]http://puu.sh/mJpM.pn/img]

A CM here made a spreadsheet that tracks the number of players according to the “people currently online” counter on the homepage, so this will give you a specific count for the past 4-5 months. I tried finding an option to average out the results so it would be more obvious, but according to these numbers gathered there has been an increase over the past few months.

Specifically within the past two months, it has gone up quite a bit :o Maybe it’s just bots coming back that had been nuked? There will be another nuke within the next few weeks, so it’ll be interesting to see what happens then.

Do you have one for the whole decade? 2000-2010?
[/quote]
no, exemplar just recently learned about google docs[/quote]

this :p[quote=“Rodgerwilco, post:20, topic:437568”][quote author=m1lkman link=topic=540274.msg3957375#msg3957375 date=1332894010]
Times have changed. Players who know what runescape is tell their friends, “runescape.com” not “google runescape”. They download the client and play without opening a browser.
[/quote]

How about the people who need to search an npc, quest, skill calculator, guides, websites, hacks, cheats, etc etc etc. The less searches = the less interest. Less interest = less players. It’s quite obvious rs has lost players.[/quote]

I can’t speak for everyone else but whenever I’m Googling something Runescape related, I type my query + rswiki, “agility rswiki” for example

Read full topic
